    "summary": "Henry Schirmer is CFO (Chief Financial Officer) of Randstad Group, a global HR services industry leader. Randstad has north of 40.000 corporate employees and 4,800 branches in 39 countries. Randstad generates revenue of \u20ac 23.7 billion in 2019. In this role he is responsible for Global Finance & Accounting, Business Control, M&A, Tax, Treasury, Business Risk & Audit, Legal and Investor Relations. \n\nBefore his role at Randstad he was the Executive Vice President and CFO of Unilever Europe. In his 20+ year career, Mr. Schirmer has gained international management and leadership experience in the fast moving consumer goods industry and industrial sector under public and private equity ownership. Prior positions include Senior Vice President, Finance of Unilever North America, Vice President, Finance of Unilever\u2019s operations in Germany, Austria and Switzerland, CFO of Birdseye Iglo Group and Vice President of mergers and acquisitions of Unilever, where he was responsible for deal origination and execution across Unilever\u2019s global portfolio.\n\nMr. Schirmer holds a Master\u2019s degree in Industrial Engineering and Management from the Technical University of Karlsruhe (Karlsruhe Institute of Technology) in Germany.",
